event_investment_decisions.event_description:
In the upcoming MLB game, scheduled for September 17 at 7:40PM ET:
If the Los Angeles Angels win, the market will resolve to “Angels”.
If the Milwaukee Brewers win, the market will resolve to “Brewers”.
If the game is postponed, this market will remain open until the game has been completed.
If the game is canceled entirely, with no make-up game, this market will resolve 50-50.
To know when a postponed game will be played, please check the home team's schedule on MLB.com for the listed team and look for the game described as a makeup game.

decision.rationale: The Brewers won the game 9-2, so this market will resolve to 'Brewers'. The current price of 0.0355 for the Angels correctly reflects their low probability of winning. There is no mispricing here, so no bet is warranted.

The Brewers won by 7 runs (9-2), which is well over the 1.5 run spread. This market will resolve to 'Yes' for Milwaukee Brewers. The current price of 0.85 seems reasonable given the large margin of victory. There is no significant mispricing, so no bet is warranted.

The total runs scored were 11 (9 by Brewers + 2 by Angels), which is over 7.5. This market will resolve to 'Over'. The current price of 0.82 seems reasonable given the high-scoring game. There is no significant mispricing, so no bet is warranted.

decision.rationale: Both teams scored 0 runs in the first inning, so this market will resolve to 'Yes'. The current price for 'Yes' is 0.9955, which seems extremely high. Historically, it's common for baseball games to have scoreless first innings. A price of 0.9955 implies only a 0.45% chance of at least one run being scored in the first inning, which seems too extreme. This appears to be a mispricing that we can take advantage of by betting on 'Yes'.

event_investment_decisions.event_description:
The FED interest rates are defined in this market by the upper bound of the target federal funds range. The decisions on the target federal fund range are made by the Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meetings.

This market will resolve to the amount of basis points the upper bound of the target federal funds rate is changed by versus the level it was prior to the Federal Reserve's October 2025 meeting.

If the target federal funds rate is changed to a level not expressed in the displayed options, the change will be rounded up to the nearest 25 and will resolve to the relevant bracket. (e.g. if there's a cut/increase of 12.5 bps it will be considered to be 25 bps)

The resolution source for this market is the FOMC’s statement after its meeting scheduled for October 28 - 29, 2025 according to the official calendar: https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/fomccalendars.htm.

The level and change of the target federal funds rate is also published at the official website of the Federal Reserve at https://www.federalreserve.gov/monetarypolicy/openmarket.htm.

This market may resolve as soon as the FOMC’s statement for their October meeting with relevant data is issued. If no statement is released by the end date of the next scheduled meeting, this market will resolve to the "No change" bracket.

decision.rationale: The market is for a 50+ bps decrease in October 2025. Given that the Fed just cut rates in September and signaled more modest cuts, a 50+ bps cut in October seems unlikely. The current price of 0.0735 seems reasonable, but we'll take a small position against it just in case the market is overestimating this probability.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: Fed decreases interest rates by 50+ bps after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: The market is for a 25 bps decrease in October 2025. The Fed just cut rates by 25 bps in September and signaled more cuts ahead. A 25 bps cut in October seems plausible, but the current price of 0.785 seems high given that the Fed has already cut rates recently. We estimate a lower probability and will bet against this outcome.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: Fed decreases interest rates by 25 bps after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: The market is for no change in October 2025. With the Fed having just cut rates in September and signaling more cuts, no change seems unlikely. The current price of 0.145 reflects this low probability and seems reasonable. We'll make a small bet in favor of this outcome.

market_investment_decisions.market_question: No change in Fed interest rates after October 2025 meeting?

decision.rationale: The market is for a 25+ bps increase in October 2025. With the Fed cutting rates and signaling more cuts, an increase is highly unlikely. The current price of 0.0075 is very low and seems reasonable. We'll make a small bet against this outcome.
